title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a plan that outputs all creditors that do not have "SLETTET" in their name, and that have an id between 193000 and 194000. Output in textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log:
Build a plan to:
- Read the creditors dataset.
- Filter records where:
  - id is between 193000 and 194000 (inclusive), and
  - the name field does not contain the substring "SLETTET".
- Output all fields of the matching creditor records to a text file.

log.thoughts: Need to filter creditors by name not containing 'SLETTET' and creditor_id range 193000-194000; only the creditor table contains these fields.

steps.detailed_description: Load the 'creditor' table via JDBC input, selecting all columns: creditor_id (integer), name (text), creditor_type (text). Output: full creditor dataset.

Filter the creditor records to keep only rows where creditor_id is between 193000 and 194000 inclusive, and the name field does NOT contain the substring 'SLETTET' (case-sensitive containment check). Input: full creditor dataset. Output: filtered creditor dataset with the same columns.
Write all fields of the filtered creditor records (creditor_id, name, creditor_type) to a text file output.

log.thoughts: The task requires reading one table, applying a compound filter, and writing the result, so three concise steps are sufficient.

title: Class: StepHandler created step dependencies and queue

log.thoughts: Loaded the creditor table via a single JDBC input operator selecting the specified columns. No downstream steps yet, so left output empty for future chaining.

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = r.getField(1).toString; id >= 193000 && id <= 194000 && !name.contains("SLETTET") }

log.thoughts: Loaded creditor table via JDBC (op 1) and applied the specified filter on id range and name not containing 'SLETTET' (op 2). IDs start at 1, last op has empty output for chaining by future steps.

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = r.getField(1).toString; id >= 193000 && id <= 194000 && !name.contains("SLETTET") }
(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = r.getField(1).toString; val ctype = r.getField(2).toString; s"${id} | ${name} | ${ctype}" }

log.thoughts: Started with JDBC input of creditor table (step 1), applied required filter on id range and name substring (step 2), then mapped Records to strings for file output and added textFileOutput (step 3). IDs are continuous and references consistent.
